WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:11.052 --> 00:00:12.679 position:50% align:center
[gasp]

00:00:16.641 --> 00:00:18.018 position:50% align:center
Yuito?

00:00:20.395 --> 00:00:22.063 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:00:22.147 --> 00:00:24.607 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:00:24.691 --> 00:00:25.984 position:50% align:center
[LUKA]
He can't move...

00:00:26.067 --> 00:00:28.194 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI]
What's happening to him?

00:00:28.278 --> 00:00:30.280 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:00:30.363 --> 00:00:31.823 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
This is bad.

00:00:35.660 --> 00:00:37.704 position:50% align:center
Yuito and his team
are up ahead.

00:00:37.787 --> 00:00:41.750 position:50% align:center
Looks like they're interfacing
with the BABE city-computer.

00:00:41.833 --> 00:00:43.626 position:50% align:center
Huh, I'm locked out.

00:00:43.710 --> 00:00:45.045 position:50% align:center
[KASANE gasps]

00:00:45.128 --> 00:00:47.922 position:50% align:center
[KAGERO] BABE is one of
Togetsu's most important assets,

00:00:48.006 --> 00:00:49.341 position:50% align:center
so it makes sense that
they wouldn't let us

00:00:49.424 --> 00:00:51.134 position:50% align:center
just waltz right in.

00:00:51.217 --> 00:00:53.928 position:50% align:center
[KASANE gasps]
Yuito, you there?

00:00:56.097 --> 00:01:00.018 position:50% align:center
Wait. It connected...
but it's strange.

00:01:00.101 --> 00:01:02.354 position:50% align:center
Communications should've
been locked down.

00:01:02.437 --> 00:01:03.563 position:50% align:center
You sure you actually--

00:01:03.646 --> 00:01:06.524 position:50% align:center
Trust me. I don't know
why it's happening,

00:01:06.608 --> 00:01:10.445 position:50% align:center
but I can feel Yuito's
brainwaves, somehow.

00:01:10.528 --> 00:01:12.781 position:50% align:center
[KASANE gasps]
Oh, no.

00:01:12.864 --> 00:01:14.157 position:50% align:center
What's wrong?

00:01:14.240 --> 00:01:17.160 position:50% align:center
We have to go! They're trying
to hijack his brain!

00:01:17.243 --> 00:01:18.078 position:50% align:center
Really?

00:01:18.161 --> 00:01:20.872 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Yuito!

00:01:20.955 --> 00:01:22.499 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:01:22.582 --> 00:01:25.794 position:50% align:center
[KASANE] 
Yuito... Yuito!

00:01:28.338 --> 00:01:30.298 position:50% align:center
Can you hear me? Yuito!

00:01:30.382 --> 00:01:31.424 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:01:31.508 --> 00:01:33.385 position:50% align:center
You have to sever
the connection now!

00:01:33.468 --> 00:01:38.473 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]
Come on, move. I have to move!

00:01:38.556 --> 00:01:39.766 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]

00:01:41.476 --> 00:01:43.728 position:50% align:center
Hey guys! Please, wake up!

00:01:43.812 --> 00:01:46.690 position:50% align:center
Hanabi...! Tsugumi!

00:01:46.773 --> 00:01:47.982 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:01:49.984 --> 00:01:51.194 position:50% align:center
[shouts]

00:01:52.654 --> 00:01:57.075 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Wait, what was that?

00:01:57.158 --> 00:01:59.577 position:50% align:center
They... They tried
to hijack my brain.

00:01:59.661 --> 00:02:00.745 position:50% align:center
[HANABI]

00:02:00.829 --> 00:02:03.289 position:50% align:center
I knew that something
didn't feel right.

00:02:03.373 --> 00:02:06.710 position:50% align:center
I bet this is what they were
trying to do from the start.

00:02:06.793 --> 00:02:09.337 position:50% align:center
What are they planning
to do with him?

00:02:09.421 --> 00:02:11.089 position:50% align:center
Kasane. Thank you.

00:02:11.172 --> 00:02:12.424 position:50% align:center
[LUKA gasps]

00:02:12.507 --> 00:02:15.343 position:50% align:center
She was able to get through
to me over Brain Talk.

00:02:15.427 --> 00:02:18.555 position:50% align:center
Kasane? Why is she in Togetsu?

00:02:18.638 --> 00:02:19.723 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:02:19.806 --> 00:02:21.266 position:50% align:center
You have to be careful.

00:02:21.349 --> 00:02:24.102 position:50% align:center
They're after the Red
Strings we both have.

00:02:24.185 --> 00:02:25.478 position:50% align:center
Say what?

00:02:25.562 --> 00:02:27.605 position:50% align:center
Red strings? What's that?

00:02:27.689 --> 00:02:29.607 position:50% align:center
Right. We need to leave.

00:02:29.691 --> 00:02:32.110 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Hold on. Before you go.

00:02:32.193 --> 00:02:34.612 position:50% align:center
I need you to help me
with something.

00:02:34.696 --> 00:02:36.156 position:50% align:center
It's Arashi and the others.

00:02:36.239 --> 00:02:38.742 position:50% align:center
They're being held
somewhere nearby.

00:02:38.825 --> 00:02:40.243 position:50% align:center
With the BABE terminal.

00:02:40.326 --> 00:02:42.662 position:50% align:center
You should be able to
open the facility's locks.

00:02:42.746 --> 00:02:43.747 position:50% align:center
Please, Yuito.

00:02:43.830 --> 00:02:47.250 position:50% align:center
Okay. We'll try.

00:02:47.334 --> 00:02:48.626 position:50% align:center
I hope they're alright.

00:02:48.710 --> 00:02:49.961 position:50% align:center
Are you sure?

00:02:50.045 --> 00:02:52.505 position:50% align:center
How do we know if she's
on our side or not?

00:02:52.589 --> 00:02:56.885 position:50% align:center
No, she wouldn't have saved
us if she wanted me dead.

00:02:59.763 --> 00:03:01.556 position:50% align:center
[LUKA]
Here's the admin access.

00:03:01.639 --> 00:03:03.391 position:50% align:center
I'll get us in.

00:03:03.475 --> 00:03:04.392 position:50% align:center
Good plan.

00:03:04.476 --> 00:03:05.894 position:50% align:center
Will that work?

00:03:05.977 --> 00:03:08.021 position:50% align:center
It's the only chance we've got.

00:03:08.104 --> 00:03:09.814 position:50% align:center
We can help Kasane,

00:03:09.898 --> 00:03:12.400 position:50% align:center
but we also need to make
sure we can make it out.

00:03:12.484 --> 00:03:15.236 position:50% align:center
Right. Hold on, I'm almost done.

00:03:15.320 --> 00:03:16.529 position:50% align:center
And there.

00:03:18.198 --> 00:03:19.157 position:50% align:center
[alarms]

00:03:19.240 --> 00:03:20.575 position:50% align:center
[HANABI gasps]

00:03:20.658 --> 00:03:22.035 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]

00:03:25.497 --> 00:03:30.502 position:50% align:center
♪

00:04:55.462 --> 00:04:58.840 position:50% align:center
[alarms]

00:04:58.923 --> 00:05:01.468 position:50% align:center
Yeah, I figured
that might happen.

00:05:01.551 --> 00:05:03.720 position:50% align:center
--[ARASHI] Kasane?
--Arashi!

00:05:03.803 --> 00:05:06.473 position:50% align:center
So, you guys are
still alive, huh?

00:05:06.556 --> 00:05:08.808 position:50% align:center
I've managed to
pinpoint your location.

00:05:08.892 --> 00:05:11.436 position:50% align:center
We'll use Kagero's
powers to get to you.

00:05:11.519 --> 00:05:13.188 position:50% align:center
Sit tight until then.

00:05:19.194 --> 00:05:22.489 position:50% align:center
Come on! Does she really
expect us to wait around?

00:05:22.572 --> 00:05:25.116 position:50% align:center
If she's on her way,
there's no point in leaving.

00:05:25.200 --> 00:05:26.493 position:50% align:center
This sucks.

00:05:26.576 --> 00:05:27.744 position:50% align:center
[ALL pant]

00:05:27.827 --> 00:05:30.246 position:50% align:center
[WATARU] Hurry! The exit
is just up ahead!

00:05:33.833 --> 00:05:34.584 position:50% align:center
Heads up!

00:05:34.668 --> 00:05:36.461 position:50% align:center
Get the hell out of our way!

00:05:37.629 --> 00:05:38.838 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:05:45.303 --> 00:05:48.306 position:50% align:center
Huh...? Kasane?

00:05:51.810 --> 00:05:54.145 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]

00:05:54.229 --> 00:05:56.398 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Huh? What's going on?

00:05:56.481 --> 00:05:58.525 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:05:58.608 --> 00:06:00.694 position:50% align:center
Wait a sec. That's not--

00:06:00.777 --> 00:06:02.320 position:50% align:center
[WATARU] There are more
coming to cut you off.

00:06:02.404 --> 00:06:03.488 position:50% align:center
Keep moving!

00:06:03.571 --> 00:06:06.282 position:50% align:center
[YUITO grunts]
Break through them!

00:06:06.366 --> 00:06:08.284 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA grunts]

00:06:15.709 --> 00:06:22.215 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:06:22.298 --> 00:06:24.509 position:50% align:center
Why did they look like Kasane?

00:06:24.592 --> 00:06:25.969 position:50% align:center
They're Design Children.

00:06:26.052 --> 00:06:29.180 position:50% align:center
Huh? But I thought
Kasane was from Suoh?

00:06:29.264 --> 00:06:31.891 position:50% align:center
Are you telling me that she's
one of those things, too?

00:06:31.975 --> 00:06:34.644 position:50% align:center
I get it,
it's hard to believe.

00:06:34.728 --> 00:06:38.314 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI gasps] Enemies
incoming. From behind us!

00:06:38.398 --> 00:06:42.402 position:50% align:center
[GEMMA grunts] Right now, we
need to focus on getting out.

00:06:42.485 --> 00:06:43.695 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:06:51.119 --> 00:06:52.912 position:50% align:center
[KAGERO sighs]
Wow.

00:06:52.996 --> 00:06:56.416 position:50% align:center
Things were starting to look
a little dicey in there, huh?

00:06:56.499 --> 00:06:59.044 position:50% align:center
Great job, Kagero!
You saved the day!

00:06:59.127 --> 00:07:02.005 position:50% align:center
Hey, you know, you're right!
I did save everyone!

00:07:02.088 --> 00:07:03.465 position:50% align:center
It's no biggie.

00:07:03.548 --> 00:07:05.425 position:50% align:center
You can thank me after
we get outta here.

00:07:05.508 --> 00:07:08.011 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN] Tsk! This isn't
a time for jokes.

00:07:08.094 --> 00:07:10.180 position:50% align:center
We're still in enemy territory.

00:07:10.263 --> 00:07:13.266 position:50% align:center
I wouldn't worry too much
about getting found out.

00:07:13.350 --> 00:07:16.186 position:50% align:center
Since they're already
here waiting for us.

00:07:16.269 --> 00:07:18.396 position:50% align:center
Isn't that right, Kyoka?

00:07:23.777 --> 00:07:26.821 position:50% align:center
Kyoka. Just let us through.

00:07:26.905 --> 00:07:30.325 position:50% align:center
In order for us to correct
the wrongs of this reality,

00:07:30.408 --> 00:07:33.286 position:50% align:center
we can't allow you to leave.
Sorry, Kasane.

00:07:39.000 --> 00:07:40.210 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:07:43.630 --> 00:07:45.340 position:50% align:center
[KYOKA grunts]

00:07:47.592 --> 00:07:49.594 position:50% align:center
[KASANE] Kyoka, I don't
want to fight you!

00:07:49.678 --> 00:07:50.887 position:50% align:center
[KYOKA gasps]

00:07:52.931 --> 00:07:53.807 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN grunts]

00:07:53.890 --> 00:07:55.100 position:50% align:center
[KAGERO grunts]

00:07:56.434 --> 00:07:57.727 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Why are you doing this?

00:07:57.811 --> 00:08:00.355 position:50% align:center
[KYOKA] Togetsu's wish.
Is to use your Red Strings

00:08:00.438 --> 00:08:02.691 position:50% align:center
to forge the future
as it should be!

00:08:03.858 --> 00:08:06.361 position:50% align:center
[KASANE] The Kyoka I look
up to wouldn't do this!

00:08:06.444 --> 00:08:08.655 position:50% align:center
It isn't too late to
come back to us!

00:08:08.738 --> 00:08:10.699 position:50% align:center
[KYOKA gasps]

00:08:10.782 --> 00:08:11.950 position:50% align:center
[KAGERO]
Wow, Kasane.

00:08:12.033 --> 00:08:14.285 position:50% align:center
I never took you
for an optimist.

00:08:14.369 --> 00:08:16.538 position:50% align:center
It'll take more than
that to sway her.

00:08:16.621 --> 00:08:17.914 position:50% align:center
I can't be certain of it,

00:08:17.997 --> 00:08:21.418 position:50% align:center
but my guess is her sense
of self was constructed.

00:08:21.501 --> 00:08:24.379 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Why would they do that?

00:08:24.462 --> 00:08:25.463 position:50% align:center
[KYOKA grunts]

00:08:25.547 --> 00:08:27.048 position:50% align:center
[KASANE groans]

00:08:33.805 --> 00:08:35.098 position:50% align:center
[ARASHI]
Kasane!

00:08:36.349 --> 00:08:37.475 position:50% align:center
[KYOKA gasps]

00:08:41.229 --> 00:08:45.066 position:50% align:center
What have I done? This isn't me.

00:08:47.694 --> 00:08:49.404 position:50% align:center
[KYOKA gasps]

00:08:49.487 --> 00:08:51.281 position:50% align:center
I'm not Pope.

00:08:51.364 --> 00:08:54.117 position:50% align:center
And I refuse to be
her pawn any longer.

00:08:54.200 --> 00:08:56.953 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN] Wait. What the hell
are you talking about, Kyoka?

00:08:57.037 --> 00:09:00.206 position:50% align:center
That's right.
My name is Kyoka Eden.

00:09:00.290 --> 00:09:02.417 position:50% align:center
I was part of the OSF.

00:09:02.500 --> 00:09:04.836 position:50% align:center
And I loved serving
alongside you all.

00:09:04.919 --> 00:09:08.048 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN gasps] Then why did
you betray us back there?

00:09:08.131 --> 00:09:09.966 position:50% align:center
And just who is this Pope?

00:09:10.050 --> 00:09:11.718 position:50% align:center
[KASANE gasps]

00:09:11.801 --> 00:09:13.928 position:50% align:center
I...

00:09:14.012 --> 00:09:16.097 position:50% align:center
[KAGERO]
She's talking about Hitoyo Pope.

00:09:16.181 --> 00:09:17.974 position:50% align:center
The founder of
the Togetsu faith.

00:09:18.058 --> 00:09:20.268 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:09:20.352 --> 00:09:22.687 position:50% align:center
[KAGERO] Doctor Pope was
a neuroscience expert.

00:09:22.771 --> 00:09:25.732 position:50% align:center
What's more, Kyoka is one
of the Design Children based

00:09:25.815 --> 00:09:28.651 position:50% align:center
on her DNA. A genetic clone.

00:09:30.528 --> 00:09:32.447 position:50% align:center
[KYOKA]
He's right and not only that,

00:09:32.530 --> 00:09:34.157 position:50% align:center
I share some of her memories.

00:09:34.240 --> 00:09:35.450 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN]
Huh?

00:09:37.494 --> 00:09:41.081 position:50% align:center
That's why... I did whatever
Pope wanted me to do.

00:09:41.164 --> 00:09:46.086 position:50% align:center
I did my best to protect you.
And nurture your growth.

00:09:46.169 --> 00:09:48.672 position:50% align:center
I waited for the Red
Strings to awaken in you.

00:09:48.755 --> 00:09:51.966 position:50% align:center
So that I could bring you
back home to Togetsu.

00:09:53.385 --> 00:09:58.181 position:50% align:center
And then, Pope's dream
would finally be achieved.

00:09:58.264 --> 00:10:03.937 position:50% align:center
I can't tell anymore,
who, or even what I am.

00:10:04.020 --> 00:10:06.064 position:50% align:center
[KASANE gasps]

00:10:06.147 --> 00:10:09.609 position:50% align:center
Listen, Kyoka. You're not alone.

00:10:09.693 --> 00:10:12.153 position:50% align:center
I know what it's like
to lose yourself.

00:10:12.237 --> 00:10:15.115 position:50% align:center
To almost forget
who you really are.

00:10:15.198 --> 00:10:17.033 position:50% align:center
[WAKANA] Do you honestly
think this is what's best

00:10:17.117 --> 00:10:19.244 position:50% align:center
for the future?

00:10:19.327 --> 00:10:21.496 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE BELIEVER A] This girl
is one of the Design Children

00:10:21.579 --> 00:10:23.915 position:50% align:center
created for the
advancement of the world.

00:10:23.998 --> 00:10:26.876 position:50% align:center
But somehow,
even if you do forget,

00:10:26.960 --> 00:10:30.296 position:50% align:center
a part of you stays the same.
Isn't that right?

00:10:34.676 --> 00:10:36.594 position:50% align:center
Kasane...

00:10:36.678 --> 00:10:41.016 position:50% align:center
There are memories I hold dear
and when I think of them,

00:10:41.099 --> 00:10:42.726 position:50% align:center
I know who I really am.

00:10:42.809 --> 00:10:45.020 position:50% align:center
No matter what,
I'm Kasane Randall.

00:10:45.103 --> 00:10:46.563 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:10:46.646 --> 00:10:50.025 position:50% align:center
[KASANE inhales] Kyoka, I know
that it's the same for you.

00:10:51.192 --> 00:10:53.445 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
You accepted me right away.

00:10:53.528 --> 00:10:56.197 position:50% align:center
And helped make
everyone feel welcomed.

00:10:56.281 --> 00:10:58.116 position:50% align:center
You were always so kind.

00:10:58.199 --> 00:11:00.452 position:50% align:center
And patient.

00:11:00.535 --> 00:11:03.913 position:50% align:center
You're an irreplaceable
member of the team

00:11:03.997 --> 00:11:06.833 position:50% align:center
and we would have never
made it this far without you.

00:11:08.543 --> 00:11:09.711 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:11:09.794 --> 00:11:11.629 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
I don't care what happens,

00:11:11.713 --> 00:11:15.050 position:50% align:center
You'll always be Kyoka Eden,
the captain who taught me

00:11:15.133 --> 00:11:16.718 position:50% align:center
how to be a leader.

00:11:20.055 --> 00:11:22.432 position:50% align:center
And nothing is going
to change that.

00:11:22.515 --> 00:11:26.353 position:50% align:center
[gasps, whimpers]

00:11:26.436 --> 00:11:28.021 position:50% align:center
Kasane, I--

00:11:44.329 --> 00:11:47.457 position:50% align:center
[KYOKA]
I'm sorry, it's all my fault.

00:11:47.540 --> 00:11:49.542 position:50% align:center
We should have never
have come here.

00:11:49.626 --> 00:11:51.378 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
It's okay.

00:11:51.461 --> 00:11:53.254 position:50% align:center
It's a happy ending after all.

00:11:53.338 --> 00:11:55.298 position:50% align:center
No, it's still
too early to tell.

00:11:55.382 --> 00:11:57.008 position:50% align:center
This could be an act
to lower our guard.

00:11:57.092 --> 00:11:58.259 position:50% align:center
Arashi!

00:11:58.343 --> 00:11:59.928 position:50% align:center
She's already tricked
everyone here.

00:12:00.011 --> 00:12:02.389 position:50% align:center
Don't tell me you were moved
by her tearful apology?

00:12:02.472 --> 00:12:04.766 position:50% align:center
I'd much rather be
safe than sorry.

00:12:04.849 --> 00:12:08.895 position:50% align:center
It's alright. It's only
natural you'd be suspicious.

00:12:08.978 --> 00:12:12.482 position:50% align:center
But what we think
isn't important, right?

00:12:12.565 --> 00:12:15.402 position:50% align:center
What is it that you want to do?

00:12:15.485 --> 00:12:16.486 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:12:16.569 --> 00:12:17.904 position:50% align:center
Since you don't wanna fight,

00:12:17.987 --> 00:12:20.156 position:50% align:center
are you gonna go
back to Togetsu?

00:12:20.240 --> 00:12:23.910 position:50% align:center
Honestly? I don't really know.

00:12:26.371 --> 00:12:28.415 position:50% align:center
I'm nothing more than a clone.

00:12:28.498 --> 00:12:31.918 position:50% align:center
I was created solely for
one specific purpose.

00:12:32.002 --> 00:12:34.754 position:50% align:center
I was willing to do
anything to accomplish it,

00:12:34.838 --> 00:12:38.216 position:50% align:center
even give my own life.

00:12:38.299 --> 00:12:41.302 position:50% align:center
Bringing you here was my
entire reason for existing.

00:12:41.386 --> 00:12:43.054 position:50% align:center
But after meeting you all,

00:12:43.138 --> 00:12:46.433 position:50% align:center
I've discovered something
else I want to do.

00:12:46.516 --> 00:12:49.936 position:50% align:center
I know full well I don't have
the right to ask for anything.

00:12:50.020 --> 00:12:53.356 position:50% align:center
And what I've done to you
all can't be forgiven.

00:12:53.440 --> 00:12:56.943 position:50% align:center
But still, All I want is
to stay by your sides.

00:12:57.027 --> 00:13:00.447 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:13:00.530 --> 00:13:03.283 position:50% align:center
I get that you probably
don't believe me,

00:13:03.366 --> 00:13:05.368 position:50% align:center
but let me prove it to you.

00:13:05.452 --> 00:13:11.082 position:50% align:center
I want to protect those I hold
dear, to see everyone smile.

00:13:11.166 --> 00:13:13.752 position:50% align:center
Good. I believe you.

00:13:13.835 --> 00:13:16.504 position:50% align:center
You may have had other motives,
but all the kindness

00:13:16.588 --> 00:13:19.966 position:50% align:center
you showed us has always
been the real thing.

00:13:20.050 --> 00:13:21.217 position:50% align:center
[KYOKA gasps]

00:13:21.301 --> 00:13:24.554 position:50% align:center
Your constant meddling
got annoying at times,

00:13:24.637 --> 00:13:26.598 position:50% align:center
but that's just you.

00:13:26.681 --> 00:13:28.725 position:50% align:center
She's right.
Everything you just said,

00:13:28.808 --> 00:13:31.686 position:50% align:center
sounded exactly like the
Kyoka I know and love.

00:13:31.770 --> 00:13:33.313 position:50% align:center
And if all that was an act,

00:13:33.396 --> 00:13:36.608 position:50% align:center
congrats, it was good
enough to fool me.

00:13:36.691 --> 00:13:38.234 position:50% align:center
Arashi.

00:13:38.318 --> 00:13:41.738 position:50% align:center
Listen. If Pope tries to
rear her little head again,

00:13:41.821 --> 00:13:44.074 position:50% align:center
You can count on me
to chop it right off.

00:13:44.157 --> 00:13:45.617 position:50% align:center
So don't worry about it.

00:13:45.700 --> 00:13:47.952 position:50% align:center
What the--? You basically
just said that you're gonna

00:13:48.036 --> 00:13:50.372 position:50% align:center
murder anybody who crosses you!

00:13:50.455 --> 00:13:53.249 position:50% align:center
And right after Kyoka opened
up her heart to us, too.

00:13:53.333 --> 00:13:55.460 position:50% align:center
At this point, I'm starting to
think it's more dangerous

00:13:55.543 --> 00:13:57.253 position:50% align:center
trusting you than her.

00:13:57.337 --> 00:13:58.755 position:50% align:center
This is just sad.

00:13:58.838 --> 00:14:01.466 position:50% align:center
I leave you alone for a bit
and you all just fall apart.

00:14:01.549 --> 00:14:02.384 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN grunts]

00:14:02.467 --> 00:14:03.760 position:50% align:center
Hey guys!

00:14:03.843 --> 00:14:06.304 position:50% align:center
I'm picking up multiple
signatures not far from you!

00:14:06.388 --> 00:14:07.681 position:50% align:center
It's Yuito's platoon.

00:14:07.764 --> 00:14:10.975 position:50% align:center
Roger. They managed
to escape, too.

00:14:11.059 --> 00:14:14.562 position:50% align:center
Hopefully, they'll be open
to exchanging information.

00:14:14.646 --> 00:14:17.649 position:50% align:center
Okay. Let's rendezvous
with them.

00:14:17.732 --> 00:14:19.067 position:50% align:center
You ready to go?

00:14:19.150 --> 00:14:20.819 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:14:20.902 --> 00:14:22.487 position:50% align:center
Goes without saying,
but we wouldn't leave

00:14:22.570 --> 00:14:26.574 position:50% align:center
one of our own behind,
isn't that right?

00:14:26.658 --> 00:14:32.831 position:50% align:center
Kasane, thank you... so much.

00:14:39.796 --> 00:14:41.965 position:50% align:center
Yuito. Are you sure
we can trust them?

00:14:42.048 --> 00:14:45.719 position:50% align:center
I'm sure. After all,
Kasane did save us back there.

00:14:45.802 --> 00:14:47.929 position:50% align:center
Even so, we can't
let our guards down.

00:14:48.013 --> 00:14:50.765 position:50% align:center
She did allegedly
kill your father.

00:14:50.849 --> 00:14:51.725 position:50% align:center
[YUITO]
Maybe.

00:14:51.808 --> 00:14:53.435 position:50% align:center
[LUKA gasps]

00:14:53.518 --> 00:14:56.146 position:50% align:center
We haven't heard her
side of the story yet.

00:14:57.605 --> 00:15:00.233 position:50% align:center
[YUITO] I know she
tried to kill me, but...

00:15:00.316 --> 00:15:02.902 position:50% align:center
...she must've had a reason.

00:15:02.986 --> 00:15:05.613 position:50% align:center
Just up ahead.
Seems like they beat us here.

00:15:09.117 --> 00:15:13.663 position:50% align:center
Kasane! I'm glad to
see you're all okay!

00:15:13.747 --> 00:15:16.833 position:50% align:center
We couldn't have done it
without you. Thank you.

00:15:16.916 --> 00:15:20.253 position:50% align:center
Likewise. If you hadn't gotten
through to me when you did,

00:15:20.337 --> 00:15:23.298 position:50% align:center
our minds would have
been hijacked by BABE.

00:15:23.381 --> 00:15:26.134 position:50% align:center
Tsugumi, hey!
Are you doing alright?

00:15:26.217 --> 00:15:27.469 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI]
Mm!

00:15:27.552 --> 00:15:30.972 position:50% align:center
Hey before we continue,
I wanna hear it from you.

00:15:31.056 --> 00:15:34.184 position:50% align:center
You're not going to
kill Yuito, are you?

00:15:34.267 --> 00:15:35.643 position:50% align:center
I'm not.

00:15:35.727 --> 00:15:38.897 position:50% align:center
Please believe me, I'm actually
trying to save his life.

00:15:38.980 --> 00:15:41.107 position:50% align:center
There's something much
deeper going on here

00:15:41.191 --> 00:15:43.026 position:50% align:center
and if all of us work together,

00:15:43.109 --> 00:15:45.904 position:50% align:center
we'll have a better chance
of making it out alive.

00:15:45.987 --> 00:15:49.491 position:50% align:center
But this is no place to chat.
Just follow me.

00:16:04.589 --> 00:16:06.132 position:50% align:center
[KAGERO]
There's no need to be polite.

00:16:06.216 --> 00:16:07.384 position:50% align:center
Come on in.

00:16:15.058 --> 00:16:18.144 position:50% align:center
[HANABI] What is this place?
Some sort of secret hideout?

00:16:18.228 --> 00:16:19.896 position:50% align:center
[KAGERO]
You could say that.

00:16:21.981 --> 00:16:24.776 position:50% align:center
[YUITO sighs]

00:16:24.859 --> 00:16:28.238 position:50% align:center
Kasane. Now will
you finally explain?

00:16:28.321 --> 00:16:31.074 position:50% align:center
Why exactly were you
trying to kill me?

00:16:31.157 --> 00:16:35.036 position:50% align:center
Fine. But it's a
pretty crazy story.

00:16:35.120 --> 00:16:37.622 position:50% align:center
You need to remain calm.

00:16:37.706 --> 00:16:40.875 position:50% align:center
The truth is, someone
asked me to kill you,

00:16:40.959 --> 00:16:43.294 position:50% align:center
practically begged me to.

00:16:43.378 --> 00:16:47.590 position:50% align:center
And it was you,
50 years from now.

00:16:47.674 --> 00:16:49.175 position:50% align:center
Now, take my life!

00:16:49.259 --> 00:16:52.012 position:50% align:center
Do it for the sake
of this world!

00:16:52.095 --> 00:16:54.681 position:50% align:center
For the sake of the future!

00:16:54.764 --> 00:16:57.058 position:50% align:center
I asked you? What do you mean?

00:16:57.142 --> 00:16:59.060 position:50% align:center
What? Are you crazy?

00:16:59.144 --> 00:17:01.229 position:50% align:center
I certainly don't blame you.

00:17:01.312 --> 00:17:03.940 position:50% align:center
If I hadn't seen it
myself first hand,

00:17:04.024 --> 00:17:07.569 position:50% align:center
I also would've dismissed
it as some fantasy.

00:17:07.652 --> 00:17:11.656 position:50% align:center
Remember? We were at
the Kunad Highway.

00:17:11.740 --> 00:17:14.617 position:50% align:center
We saw things that were
impossible to believe.

00:17:15.785 --> 00:17:21.082 position:50% align:center
[KASANE] Somehow, all of us were
teleported to 50 years from now.

00:17:21.166 --> 00:17:21.958 position:50% align:center
[YUITO gasps]

00:17:22.042 --> 00:17:25.045 position:50% align:center
You really saw the future?

00:17:25.128 --> 00:17:27.380 position:50% align:center
I possess the power
of the Red Strings.

00:17:27.464 --> 00:17:30.300 position:50% align:center
That's why I was
able to time travel.

00:17:30.383 --> 00:17:33.428 position:50% align:center
And I believe... Yuito does too.

00:17:33.511 --> 00:17:35.597 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:17:35.680 --> 00:17:38.475 position:50% align:center
That day, your psionic
powers formed some sort

00:17:38.558 --> 00:17:40.685 position:50% align:center
of resonance with my mine.

00:17:40.769 --> 00:17:43.396 position:50% align:center
Which ended up creating
the Kunad Gate.

00:17:43.480 --> 00:17:45.440 position:50% align:center
And 50 years from now
it'll be big enough

00:17:45.523 --> 00:17:46.983 position:50% align:center
to swallow the world.

00:17:47.067 --> 00:17:48.401 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:17:50.028 --> 00:17:54.032 position:50% align:center
But, since the Kunad Gate
is linked to your psionics,

00:17:54.115 --> 00:17:57.077 position:50% align:center
if you die, it will disappear.

00:17:57.160 --> 00:18:00.163 position:50% align:center
That's what your
future self told me.

00:18:00.246 --> 00:18:03.333 position:50% align:center
Then he asked me to kill
you before it was too late.

00:18:03.416 --> 00:18:05.960 position:50% align:center
There's no way! How?

00:18:06.044 --> 00:18:10.965 position:50% align:center
I see. My psionic power really
did have an effect on the gate.

00:18:11.049 --> 00:18:12.592 position:50% align:center
So, you knew about it?

00:18:12.676 --> 00:18:16.096 position:50% align:center
Yeah. But I didn't
want to believe it.

00:18:16.179 --> 00:18:19.182 position:50% align:center
What if every time you had one
of those horrible headaches,

00:18:19.265 --> 00:18:23.061 position:50% align:center
it was somehow related to
the gate? Could that be it?

00:18:24.145 --> 00:18:27.482 position:50% align:center
I don't know.
But my future self--

00:18:27.565 --> 00:18:29.442 position:50% align:center
I'm still...

00:18:29.526 --> 00:18:30.694 position:50% align:center
[KASANE gasps]

00:18:32.153 --> 00:18:33.238 position:50% align:center
Even in the future,

00:18:33.321 --> 00:18:35.949 position:50% align:center
I'm powerless to do
anything on my own.

00:18:36.032 --> 00:18:37.158 position:50% align:center
What a loser.

00:18:37.242 --> 00:18:40.453 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Yuito. Don't give up hope.

00:18:40.537 --> 00:18:43.498 position:50% align:center
Hey. There's something
I wanted to ask you.

00:18:43.581 --> 00:18:45.000 position:50% align:center
[KASANE gasps]

00:18:45.083 --> 00:18:48.378 position:50% align:center
Kyoka is one of the Design
Children from Togetsu, right?

00:18:48.461 --> 00:18:51.423 position:50% align:center
I wonder.
What about you, Kasane?

00:18:51.506 --> 00:18:53.675 position:50% align:center
Huh? Where'd this come from?

00:18:53.758 --> 00:18:54.843 position:50% align:center
[KAGERO gasps]

00:18:54.926 --> 00:18:58.138 position:50% align:center
It's because... back in Togetsu,

00:18:58.221 --> 00:19:00.849 position:50% align:center
we saw someone who
looked just like Kasane.

00:19:02.183 --> 00:19:06.104 position:50% align:center
Which means...
you really are one.

00:19:06.187 --> 00:19:08.982 position:50% align:center
You're right.
That might be the case.

00:19:09.065 --> 00:19:11.735 position:50% align:center
You sound like you're
not so sure of that.

00:19:11.818 --> 00:19:14.946 position:50% align:center
Some of my memories came
back to me in Togetsu.

00:19:15.030 --> 00:19:18.867 position:50% align:center
Things like my
childhood and my mother.

00:19:18.950 --> 00:19:22.037 position:50% align:center
In those memories
someone said that I was

00:19:22.120 --> 00:19:24.330 position:50% align:center
one of the Design Children.

00:19:26.082 --> 00:19:29.085 position:50% align:center
Even now, none of it
seems real to me,

00:19:29.169 --> 00:19:33.131 position:50% align:center
so I want to find out
the truth about my past.

00:19:33.214 --> 00:19:34.924 position:50% align:center
I understand.

00:19:35.008 --> 00:19:37.802 position:50% align:center
Sorry, I shouldn't
have brought it up.

00:19:37.886 --> 00:19:39.971 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
You're a kind soul, Hanabi.

00:19:40.055 --> 00:19:41.765 position:50% align:center
It's okay, I forgive you.

00:19:41.848 --> 00:19:43.266 position:50% align:center
[HANABI sighs]

00:19:43.350 --> 00:19:44.642 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Let's move on.

00:19:44.726 --> 00:19:46.436 position:50% align:center
Did you manage to
uncover anything?

00:19:46.519 --> 00:19:49.147 position:50% align:center
You might not believe
the things we found out.

00:19:49.230 --> 00:19:52.525 position:50% align:center
Yeah. Apparently, humans
first came from the moon.

00:19:52.609 --> 00:19:53.902 position:50% align:center
[KAGERO, KASANE gasp]

00:19:53.985 --> 00:19:56.154 position:50% align:center
That's impossible.
What're you saying?

00:19:56.237 --> 00:19:59.574 position:50% align:center
How about you Kasane?
Have you ever heard about it?

00:19:59.657 --> 00:20:00.950 position:50% align:center
[KASANE]
Mm.

00:20:01.034 --> 00:20:02.911 position:50% align:center
And you're absolutely certain
that's what you heard?

00:20:02.994 --> 00:20:04.871 position:50% align:center
[TSUGUMI]
Mm-- Yes.

00:20:04.954 --> 00:20:07.248 position:50% align:center
It was in Togetsu's records.

00:20:07.332 --> 00:20:09.626 position:50% align:center
Three thousand years ago,
Humankind had to escape

00:20:09.709 --> 00:20:12.045 position:50% align:center
from Earth, and so they
went to the moon.

00:20:12.128 --> 00:20:15.131 position:50% align:center
A thousand years later,
a group of them came back

00:20:15.215 --> 00:20:18.760 position:50% align:center
and founded New Himuka,
or so they claim.

00:20:18.843 --> 00:20:21.429 position:50% align:center
Honestly, I don't even know
what to believe anymore.

00:20:21.513 --> 00:20:23.431 position:50% align:center
Have you heard of
this before, Kyoka?

00:20:23.515 --> 00:20:25.684 position:50% align:center
I don't think they would
have just made it all up.

00:20:25.767 --> 00:20:28.436 position:50% align:center
He's right. You're one
of the Design Children.

00:20:28.520 --> 00:20:32.565 position:50% align:center
And earlier you said that
you had Pope's memories.

00:20:32.649 --> 00:20:35.276 position:50% align:center
I didn't retain all
of her memories,

00:20:35.360 --> 00:20:38.405 position:50% align:center
so I can't say for sure if
the story is true or not.

00:20:38.488 --> 00:20:39.781 position:50% align:center
But I do know

00:20:39.864 --> 00:20:42.200 position:50% align:center
that it matches the history
that Togetsu taught me.

00:20:42.283 --> 00:20:45.078 position:50% align:center
Seriously? Just cause
Togetsu says it's true...

00:20:45.161 --> 00:20:46.162 position:50% align:center
Hold on a sec.

00:20:46.246 --> 00:20:48.957 position:50% align:center
Togetsu's often wrong,
but not on this.

00:20:49.040 --> 00:20:50.917 position:50% align:center
That entire story is true.

00:20:51.001 --> 00:20:53.545 position:50% align:center
They did go to the moon,
and after Earth had

00:20:53.628 --> 00:20:57.215 position:50% align:center
finally recovered, they came
back and founded New Himuka.

00:20:57.298 --> 00:20:59.968 position:50% align:center
How are you sure, Kagero?

00:21:00.051 --> 00:21:03.805 position:50% align:center
Oh, my sweet Tsugumi.
Don't look at me like that.

00:21:03.888 --> 00:21:06.725 position:50% align:center
You know I can't resist
when you make that face.

00:21:06.808 --> 00:21:09.436 position:50% align:center
Kagero, there's something
that I've always wanted

00:21:09.519 --> 00:21:10.979 position:50% align:center
to ask you about.

00:21:11.062 --> 00:21:12.689 position:50% align:center
Well, can't say I blame you.

00:21:12.772 --> 00:21:13.732 position:50% align:center
Wait.

00:21:13.815 --> 00:21:15.233 position:50% align:center
What is it?

00:21:15.316 --> 00:21:17.610 position:50% align:center
The memory is pretty hazy.

00:21:17.694 --> 00:21:21.656 position:50% align:center
But I remember seeing Kagero,
or rather, Pope does.

00:21:21.740 --> 00:21:23.783 position:50% align:center
How's he in Pope's memories?

00:21:23.867 --> 00:21:26.536 position:50% align:center
Those are over 2,000 years old.

00:21:26.619 --> 00:21:29.914 position:50% align:center
Kagero. Who, or what are you?

00:21:29.998 --> 00:21:32.083 position:50% align:center
While you're at it,
what is this place?

00:21:32.167 --> 00:21:33.918 position:50% align:center
'Cause it's not
just some "hideout."

00:21:34.002 --> 00:21:36.296 position:50% align:center
Heh. You always were smart.

00:21:36.379 --> 00:21:39.674 position:50% align:center
The truth is, we're all inside
what's known as an Ark.

00:21:39.758 --> 00:21:42.427 position:50% align:center
Basically, it's a spaceship.

00:21:42.510 --> 00:21:43.303 position:50% align:center
[SHIDEN]
Wait wha--?

00:21:43.386 --> 00:21:45.180 position:50% align:center
A spaceship?

00:21:45.263 --> 00:21:47.682 position:50% align:center
It's the same one I
rode to get to Earth.

00:21:47.766 --> 00:21:50.352 position:50% align:center
Two thousand years ago, I was
part of the immigrant group

00:21:50.435 --> 00:21:52.562 position:50% align:center
that came here from the moon.

00:22:07.702 --> 00:22:11.664 position:50% align:center
[KAITO] The Sumeragi family's
dearest wish will be fulfilled.

00:22:11.748 --> 00:22:13.875 position:50% align:center
And Yuito's the key.

00:22:22.634 --> 00:22:27.514 position:50% align:center
[KAREN] This time, I won't fail.
I will save you.

00:22:27.597 --> 00:22:32.602 position:50% align:center
♪